    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-05T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-05T21:00:00-05:00" n="514"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2386: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">S. S. “Santa Elena”</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >Panama</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1939-10-05T21:00:00-05:00">October 5, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 6—3:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. I would recommend that you inform the Colombian Ambassador that if his
                    Government submits to the Council a debt settlement proposal <pb facs="0521"
                        n="513" xml:id="pg_513"/> in the general range which I understand Laylin has
                    been proposing the Department will do everything it appropriately can to secure
                    its acceptance.</p>
                <p>Our understanding is that this formula would contemplate the resumption of
                    payment on a 3% scale which would gradually rise to 4%. It might be well to
                    reserve flexibility as to the secondary details.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
